cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new queuing model for the Tactile Internet in the cloud radio access network architecture of the next generation wireless networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses resource allocation and optimization techniques to minimize transmit power while guaranteeing tolerable delay for users. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes an admission control algorithm to make the problem feasible and dynamically adjusts the fronthaul and access links to minimize transmit power. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper focuses on the Tactile Internet, which involves real-time haptic communication and interaction, and proposes a model that includes both the radio remote head and baseband processing unit queuing delays and reliability for each end-to-end connection between each pair of tactile users. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the cloud radio access network architecture of the next generation wireless networks and proposes a resource allocation problem to minimize transmit power subject to fronthaul and access limitations.
